snippet.title: Bring it Back - Eddie Said Remix [Official Video]
snippet.description:
Bring it Back - Eddie Said Remix

Five-time Golden Guitar winner, Amber Lawrence, is bringing original music back with her brand new July 30 single release. The upbeat, powerful, and stirring ‘Bring it Back’ is a timely ode to the music industry, to both the artists and the fans. It laments the loss of our old ways, with Amber musically pleading for life to soon go back to the way it was. Produced by Stuart Stuart (Sheppard, The Veronicas, Lee Kernaghan, Taylor Moss), and co-written with APRA nominee Melanie Dyer, Amber’s new single is an evolved sound we haven't yet heard across Amber's past releases. With soaring vocals and a hugely catchy melody, it is set to be a new fan favourite, and will be supported by Amber’s ‘Bring it Back’ tour commencing late 2021, and early 2022. ‘Bring it Back’ is the first taste from Amber’s 7th studio album - set for a 2022 release date.

To purchase or stream Bring it Back - Eddie Said Remix - 
https://snd.click/BringItBackRemix
To Subscribe to Amber's Youtube Channel -https://www.youtube.com/c/AmberLawren...

LYRICS
BRING IT BACK - Amber Lawrence/ Melanie Dyer

I can hear it, calling in the air tonight 
Feel the rhythm, hits me then it takes me high 
As the sun sets, feel the rumble of the crowd 
Oh how we miss this, just the chance to sing out loud 
Oh sing out loud
CHORUS
We’ve been waiting for so long, for the band to play our song 
Come on bring it back 
We’ve been told to just hang on when everything we love is gone 
Come on bring it back 
Bring it back, bring it back

There’s a soundtrack for all the moments in our lives 
It’s only music, but we need it to survive
I wanna feel alive 

So sing it loud, sing along and take it back  to what it was. 
To those days, when we raised up a cup to the stage, ‘cause

We’ve been waiting for so long for the band to play our song 
Come on bring it back 
We’ve been told to just hang on when everything we love is gone 
Cmon bring it back 

Can you hear it, calling in the air tonight
